                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17864295" author="aweisberg" created="Tue, 9 Jul 2024 17:06:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;An important thing to account for in implementing this is that when migrating from Accord to Paxos it&apos;s important that non-serial reads perform Accord key barriers just like Paxos otherwise non-serial writes that were done through Accord will not be visible since Accord may have done asynchronous commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17864747" author="aweisberg" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2024 16:54:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another thing to keep in mind is that `TxnQuery` will need validate that range reads against Accord are against ranges that are managed by Accord in the epoch that the read executes in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;`TxnQuery` also currently has a problem with its validation where it doesn&apos;t have access to the migration information for the epoch of the transaction and just has whatever the latest information is.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
